info.author: Vincent Jacques
info.description:
jacquev6_development_cycle is a Python (2.7+ and 3.3+) library to help writing scripts ran repeatedly by software developers.
It provides a framework for development phases (build, draw dependency graphs, run unit tests, etc.)
and helpers for some languages (currently Python and OCaml).

It's licensed under the `MIT license <http://choosealicense.com/licenses/mit/>`__.
It's available on the `Python package index <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/jacquev6_development_cycle>`__,
its `documentation is hosted by Python <http://pythonhosted.org/jacquev6_development_cycle>`__
and its source code is on `GitHub <https://github.com/jacquev6/jacquev6_development_cycle>`__.

Questions? Remarks? Bugs? Want to contribute? `Open an issue <https://github.com/jacquev6/jacquev6_development_cycle/issues>`__!
